German Firms Want Subsidy for Car Charging, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-04-06T18:32:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/german-firms-want-subsidy-for-car-charging-handelsblatt-says.html
German energy companies want
government incentives to build charging stations across the
country for electric cars, Handelsblatt said in a report to be
published tomorrow, citing unnamed energy company executives.  “The public charging infrastructure can’t be managed
without a loss before 2020,” Ingo Alpheus, chairman of  RWE AG (RWE) ’s
energy efficiency unit, told the newspaper in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 